Chelsea striker Tammy Abraham has joined Swansea City on a season-long loan deal, the Welsh club said on Tuesday.Abraham, who also signed a new five-year contract with his parent club, scored 26 goals in 48 games on loan at English Championship side Bristol City last season.He also scored once in four games as England&#8217;s under-21 side reached the semi-finals of the European Championship last month.The 19-year-old will join Swansea boss Paul Clement, who worked as a coach at Chelsea between 2007 and 2011.Swansea, who finished 15th in the Premier League last season, open their 2017-18 campaign at Southampton on Aug. 12.-Reuters